# Toobit.Net Conventions

This codebase uses **Toobit.Net** for Toobit cryptocurrency exchange access. Do not write raw `HttpClient` calls to Toobit endpoints.

## Client Setup Pattern

```csharp
using Toobit.Net;
using Toobit.Net.Clients;

var restClient = new ToobitRestClient(options =>
{
    options.ApiCredentials = new ToobitCredentials("API_KEY", "API_SECRET");
});
```

For public market data only, credentials are not required: `new ToobitRestClient()`.

## Result Pattern

All REST calls return `WebCallResult<T>` and WebSocket subscriptions return `CallResult<UpdateSubscription>`. Always check `.Success` before reading `.Data`.

```csharp
var tickers = await restClient.SpotApi.ExchangeData.GetTickersAsync("BTCUSDT");
if (!tickers.Success) { Console.WriteLine(tickers.Error); return; }
var price = tickers.Data.Single().LastPrice;
```

## API Surface

- `restClient.SpotApi.{ExchangeData|Account|Trading}`
- `restClient.UsdtFuturesApi.{ExchangeData|Account|Trading}`
- `socketClient.SpotApi` for spot WebSocket subscriptions
- `socketClient.UsdtFuturesApi` for USDT futures WebSocket subscriptions
- `.SharedClient` on each API root for CryptoExchange.Net SharedApis

## Order Placement

```csharp
var order = await restClient.SpotApi.Trading.PlaceOrderAsync(
    "BTCUSDT",
    OrderSide.Buy,
    OrderType.Limit,
    quantity: 0.001m,
    timeInForce: TimeInForce.GoodTillCanceled,
    price: 50000m);
```

USDT futures symbols use contract names such as `ETH-SWAP-USDT`:

```csharp
var futuresOrder = await restClient.UsdtFuturesApi.Trading.PlaceOrderAsync(
    "ETH-SWAP-USDT",
    FuturesOrderSide.BuyOpen,
    FuturesNewOrderType.Limit,
    quantity: 10,
    price: 2000m,
    timeInForce: TimeInForce.GoodTillCanceled);
```

## WebSocket Pattern

```csharp
var socketClient = new ToobitSocketClient();
var sub = await socketClient.SpotApi.SubscribeToTickerUpdatesAsync(
    "BTCUSDT",
    update => { Console.WriteLine(update.Data.LastPrice); });
if (!sub.Success) { Console.WriteLine(sub.Error); return; }

await socketClient.UnsubscribeAsync(sub.Data);
```

## Multi-Exchange Code

For exchange-agnostic code, use `CryptoExchange.Net.SharedApis` from `.SharedClient`.

```csharp
using CryptoExchange.Net.SharedApis;

var shared = new ToobitRestClient().SpotApi.SharedClient;
var ticker = await shared.GetSpotTickerAsync(
    new GetTickerRequest(new SharedSymbol(TradingMode.Spot, "BTC", "USDT")));
```

## Hard Rules

- Never write raw `HttpClient` to Toobit endpoints.
- Never use `.Result` or `.Wait()`.
- Never instantiate clients per request; reuse or use DI.
- Never skip checking `WebCallResult.Success`.
- Never use `ApiCredentials` in Toobit examples; use `ToobitCredentials`.
- Never invent APIs not present in `Toobit.Net/Interfaces/Clients/**`.
- Always store WebSocket subscriptions and unsubscribe on shutdown.
- Use `ToobitEnvironment.Live` or `ToobitEnvironment.CreateCustom`; no testnet environment is defined in source.

